(66455, 'Good boy.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66456, 'When I first prowled these forests I had a pack that followed me, they were my kin, and were loyal. I grew restless of their imperfections, and figured I could do better alone. I hunted, and fought with great glory, but I abandoned those close.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66457, 'I was ambushed by a group of bear, and retreated to this very waterfall, where I was cornered, and alone, slain, only to now walk this world in a much different form. Had I kept my loyalties, and stayed with my pack, perhaps I would not have met an untimely fate. Do you understand what it is I teach you young one? You can be as powerful as the mountains, but if you are alone, you will eventually fall.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66458, 'Theramore was weak, to side with the Horde is betrayal after all who died! We will not be stopped so easily, the Vengeful Mariner will not forget!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66459, 'Oh yes, a sizable force moved here recently... Very recently. They are the Grimtotem Tauren, though. At odds with the horde, as far as I am concerned. Good. Let them fight among themselves.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66460, 'A Tauren? Well, I haven\'t seen any in a long time here. I heard something about Grimtotem in the north? You could have greater success asking closer to the Brackenwall Village. Maybe they know of some Tauren newcomers.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66461, 'Let me think... No, I haven\'t seen any come here recently. Brackenwall Village is a remote outpost, and they barely have anything to trade. On the other hand, I remember one tauren fellow living in Brackenwall. We fought side by side during the siege... Haven\'t seen him in ages. He probably drowned in the swamp.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66462, 'Oh, you will regret doing that, Dear.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66463, 'Thanks for what you\'ve done. The memories I hold in that church will not be forgotten, and perhaps, in time, there can be more made there when the land heals and the crops are sown. If the light is so gracious, we may have such a future, farewell, may your travels be safe now, ya hear?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66464, 'Without your effort we would have had to start fresh all over again, those blasted buzzards ruin everything!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66465, 'You are now blessed, you are the Earthstrider of our kin, the first to walk amongst us as an outsider, we honor you and your aid to the Gelkis cause.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66466, 'You make this old man proud, kid... Not only did you take over those oilfields like it was your own backyard, but you\'ve proudly delivered it into the Union\'s hands, with employees at that. That\'s right, some of the survivors even agreed to join us! You\'ve made our little town just a bit safer, well as safe as it could be!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66467, 'All is well, enjoying some ale, the views of southern lasses, and enjoying the weather on dry land. He should know me not to cause trouble in foreign lands.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66468, 'Check in on me? Haha! I aint causing no trouble, that goody-two-shoes Milldough should learn to have some fun, all I am doing is exploring, this place is much different then Boralus after all.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66469, 'A few weeks ago Kul Tiras was allowed embassy within the city of Stormwind, given by Bolvar Fordragon in an attempt to improve diplomacy between the two nations.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66470, 'While things seem to be going fairly well, it is quite obvious to many that Kul Tiras is still very stubborn on their ideals and traditions, their sanctity of honor, and respect for the fallen is on par with many of the most noble paladin.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66471, 'As of current, there has been no consensus, Stormwind is not looking to be dragged into a war without good reason, I am under good authority and good information to inform of no cooperation between Kul Tiras, and the Alliance in this matter. This \'invasion\' you are facing is, by our eyes, up to Thrall to handle, and deal with as he seeks fit.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66472, 'The SI:7 has given me clear authority to pass along this information for the better interest of both parties. Bring this to your leader, and let him know.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66473, 'Baha! A true soldier of the Horde! One of grit, and steel, no match for those Kul Tirans!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66474, 'Durotar stands strong, no human shall break the might of the Horde!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66476, 'Gowlfang strongest, no one dare challenge Gowlfang!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66477, 'You have kept Theramore safe, may honor follow you.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66478, 'I am Falgran Hastil, scout of Theramore. Why did you call for this meeting?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66479, 'We saw you investigate the inn. We wanted to assure you it is not the Horde\'s doing.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66480, 'We found this shield strapped to the wall of the inn. Do you have any recollection of this object?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66481, 'Let me see.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66482, 'Kagoro investigates the shield thoroughly.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66483, 'By the ancestors. Yes, I know this shield. It belonged to Wattapo, a Tauren warrior who once lived in the Brackenwall Village. He died a long time ago.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66484, 'Do you know how it could\'ve ended up in the inn? We found his grave. It was recently disturbed.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66485, 'To disturb the grave of a fallen warrior I assure you, I know nothing of this.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66486, 'It seems like someone wanted to make us blame you for the burning of the inn.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66487, 'Indeed. Have you found anything else in the investigation?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66488, 'Yes, quillboar footprints...', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66489, 'False lead.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66490, 'I see you did some work too.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66491, 'Kagoro nods.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66492, 'And the badge of one of the deserters. Paval Reethe. We couldn\'t find Reethe, though. Have you seen him, by any chance?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66493, 'This is... a delicate matter, and the actual reason I called for the meeting. Paval Reethe is dead.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66494, 'He was a deserter. While I still would\'ve preferred to arrest him and allow for a just trial, I understand that you killed him. We do not blame you.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66495, 'If it only was that simple. We knew he was connected to the burning of the inn, and we wanted to investigate him. Before he could talk... we were attacked. By Theramore soldiers. One of them bore the name Caldwell.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66496, 'Attacked? Unprovoked, by Theramore soldiers? I swear to the Light, orc. If you are lying...', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66497, 'I swear upon my ancestors and my Warchief. They killed him in cold blood. Quick arrow pierced his heart. We also barely made it out alive.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66498, 'Theramore soldiers would never... We shall investigate this. But if we find out that your words aren\'t true...', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66499, 'I am sorry for the loss of your comrades. While you investigate this, we shall follow another lead we have. Black Dragonflight.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66500, 'And we will investigate in Theramore. But be warned, orc. Your story doesn\'t add up.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66501, 'Let\'s meet here once we know more. I hope you will find truth in your city of stones.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66502, 'Kagoro! We are ready.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66503, 'Falgran.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66504, 'Kagoro, on the behalf of the Alliance and the City of Theramore, I would like to apologize for not believing you and my false accusations. We are now certain that the deserters burned the inn.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66505, 'I am relieved to hear it. Our investigation of Black Dragons yielded no results. But how did you learn of the truth?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66506, 'Through the power of magic, of course. Arts of Divination. We communed with the spirit of Paval Reethe.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66507, 'Extraordinary. Incredible sorcery, as always. But... why? Why did they burn the inn?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66508, 'Well. This is where it gets a bit complicated. The deserters were regular patrons of the inn. In their drunken state, they confessed... something to the innkeeper. In fear of the information reaching Theramore, they preferred to kill him and leave false evidence.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66509, 'The shield... Yes, it makes sense.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66510, 'Paval Reethe wanted to stop them. He may have been a deserter, but he had some of his honor still left in his heart.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66511, 'That\'s why they left him in the swamp. But, what was the information that was so precious to the deserters?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66512, 'About this, we are not sure. Something about the Vengeful Mariner, their rumored true leader. Have you heard about him?', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66513, 'Vengeful Mariner... The Ogres speak of a haunted sailor terrorizing the shores, but I doubt it\'s connected.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66514, 'We will soon bring justice to the deserters for their crimes, thank you for your information Kagoro, the horde has helped plenty in these lands.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66515, 'We believe in justice the same way you alliance do, go with honor friend.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66516, 'We should report to Captain Garran Vimes and let him know our discoveries.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66517, 'My brother Darnir was a powerful warrior, and well respected amongst those he served with. He traveled to these far lands with our family axe, and made a name for himself in the battles with the Horde during the Third War.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66518, 'A truce was established between Horde and Alliance as both factions set to head toward Hyjal. My brother would be one of the last few casualties in this conflict, as a foul orc named \'Scartusk\' ambushed him, and took our family axe as his own...', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66519, 'This orc breathes today, pardoned by the Horde, and still wielding the axe my brother carried, an heirloom to our family. I desire revenge, above all else.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66520, 'UP UP AND AWAY!', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66521, 'Corruption within Stonetalon? It does not surprise me, even here in tranquil Ashenvale, many of the native species have begun to show signs of aggression. The furbolg are the most obvious of this.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66522, 'Once our ally, the furbolg have become an enemy, attacking at sight and not hesitating to start conflict. Many druids say that nature itself is adapting to the conflict, becoming more hostile and secluded as a means to protect themselves. This could be the case in Stonetalon.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66523, 'Though here in Ashenvale, there is something else rooted deep, clawing at the foundations of all we hold sacred. I do not know what, but I can sense it...', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66524, 'That is all I know, I hope it may be of use to Maloran, we defenders of nature must keep vigilant.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66525, 'I thank you for traveling as you have. The information you have brought will prove valueable. It is up to me to find the root of the troubles now.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
(66526, 'Your armies have been defeated, and now you stand before the King of Corthan, if you desire to save the lives of the survivors, and yourself, you must swear loyalty to me, as King.', NULL, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 0),
